The Nigeria Police Force (NPF) yesterday said the planned regularization and standardization of police personnel deployed to political and public office holders, public and private companies and multinationals throughout the country has been postponed. A statement from Police spokesman, ACP Jimoh Moshood, said the enforcement of the ban has been shifted to commence on April 20. Moshood said the IGP, Ibrahim Idris after his meeting with the Commanders of Police Mobile Force (PMF), Counter Terrorism Unit (CTU) and Special Protection Unit (SPU) on March 20, shifted the enforcement earlier directed as immediately. He said the withdrawal will now take effect from April 20 to enable the Force carry out a thorough assessment of the current deployment and carry out appropriate withdrawal.